[[File:Andrew Buchanan (1798-1882).jpg|thumb]] '''Andrew Buchanan''' (10 December 1798 – 1882) was a Scottish surgeon and academic. He served as [[Regius Professor of the Institutes of Medicine]] at the [[University of Glasgow]] from 1839 to 1876.<ref name=story>{{cite web|title=Andrew Buchanan|url=http://www.universitystory.gla.ac.uk/biography/?id=WH0077&type=P|website=The University of Glasgow Story|publisher=University of Glasgow|accessdate=22 June 2017}}</ref> He practised as a surgeon at the [[Glasgow Royal Infirmary]] 1835 to 1862.<ref name="Address">{{cite web|title=Andrew Buchanan|url=http://www.glasgowwestaddress.co.uk/100_Glasgow_Men/Buchanan_Andrew.htm|website=Glasgow West Address|accessdate=22 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Andrew Buchanan|url=http://www.theglasgowstory.com/image/?inum=TGSD00025|website=Glasgow University Archive Services|publisher=University of Glasgow|accessdate=22 June 2017}}</ref> He was President of the [[Faculty of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow]] from 1879 to 1880.<ref name="story" /> He founded the ''Glasgow Medical Journal'' in 1928, and became its joint-editor.<ref name="story" /><ref name="Address" />
