The '''Hippocratic Museum''' is a [[museum]], on the [[Greece|Greek]] [[island]] of [[Kos]]. Its exhibits display the history of the Hippocratic Foundation of Kos, which is dedicated to transmitting knowledge about [[Hippocrates]], as well as founding hospitals and institutes. The ancient [[Greeks|Greek]] [[physician]] Hippocrates is believed to have been born there. The displays include some literature about the Hippocratic medicine.
